WEBVTT

00:00:01.350 --> 00:00:03.440
Her records are a complete match.

00:00:03.440 --> 00:00:06.530
The body is that of Natsumi Hayase.

00:00:06.530 --> 00:00:09.250
We found blood on your car, Mr. Hayase.

00:00:09.250 --> 00:00:11.940
You're being filed with an arrest warrant.

00:00:11.940 --> 00:00:14.190
You're being framed.

00:00:14.190 --> 00:00:16.920
Get a grip, Gido!

00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:20.950
Turn yourself in,
and you'll be punished with death.

00:00:20.950 --> 00:00:23.270
You'll be leaving your only child behind.

00:00:23.270 --> 00:00:25.670
What should I...

00:00:25.670 --> 00:00:27.640
You must reboot.

00:00:27.640 --> 00:00:30.610
I'll transform you into him.

00:00:30.610 --> 00:00:33.560
I can make you become Gido.

00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:37.320
Gido was investigating
Goroku's business undercover.

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:40.600
You'll have police intel,
and access to Goroku's circle.

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:43.930
The missing 1 billion yen remains at large, sir.

00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:49.500
Gido, I had you look into this,
when you suddenly disappeared on us.

00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:53.640
We were searching everywhere for you.

00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:56.070
And now you've come crawling back to us.

00:00:56.070 --> 00:01:00.440
It can't be. Did she trick me?

00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:03.670
Sir, there has to be a mistake.

00:01:03.670 --> 00:01:05.610
I never stole -

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:15.280
[Ayumi Gido, Reboot - Day 2]

00:01:42.680 --> 00:01:44.350
Are you okay?

00:01:53.870 --> 00:01:57.120
Spare me, I'm innocent!

00:01:57.120 --> 00:02:00.180
It's me. Ichika Kogo.

00:02:02.110 --> 00:02:04.250
I came to get you.

00:02:22.870 --> 00:02:27.090
Okay, lads. That's enough.

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:36.740
Mr. Goroku's got a message for you.

00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:41.840
If you're so innocent,
find us the real culprit, money and all.

00:02:41.840 --> 00:02:44.340
You have until midnight.

00:02:44.340 --> 00:02:46.500
You're asking the impossible.

00:02:46.500 --> 00:02:50.180
Then give us someone else to blame.

00:02:50.180 --> 00:02:55.450
Otherwise, you're not seeing
the sun rise tomorrow.

00:02:58.960 --> 00:03:03.050
If I don't resolve this today,
they'll kill me.

00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:11.590
Please, tell me what's really going on.

00:03:15.150 --> 00:03:18.920
I'll start with the money laundering.

00:03:19.770 --> 00:03:25.110
Goroku primarily deals with bettings
from foreign online casinos.

00:03:25.110 --> 00:03:26.690
[Bets from online casinos]

00:03:26.690 --> 00:03:29.200
Because online casinos are illegal in Japan,

00:03:29.200 --> 00:03:34.240
bets can't be sent to foreign banks.

00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:39.200
Instead, bets made in Japan
are sent to domestic bank accounts.

00:03:39.200 --> 00:03:42.570
Goroku's organization manages these bets.

00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:46.620
He first transfers the bets
between several corporate accounts.

00:03:46.620 --> 00:03:53.030
Once the money's trail has been lost,
he sends them to those foreign banks.

00:03:53.030 --> 00:03:57.340
He works with around 120 billion yen a year.

00:03:57.340 --> 00:03:59.570
120 billion a year?

00:03:59.570 --> 00:04:04.440
Goroku's organization also receives
a 4% cut as a commission fee.

00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:08.350
Meaning they make about 5 billion yen a year.

00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:10.010
That's still plenty.

00:04:10.010 --> 00:04:10.970
[Dubious part-time work]

00:04:10.970 --> 00:04:16.790
Goroku uses the names of part-timers
to make his many bank accounts.

00:04:16.790 --> 00:04:23.250
He manages 500 shell corporations,
and 4,000 bank accounts.

00:04:23.250 --> 00:04:25.910
If an account ever freezes
due to suspicious activity,

00:04:25.910 --> 00:04:30.280
all Goroku has to do is cut them off.

00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:34.520
Because all of these accounts
are attributed to various part-timers,

00:04:34.520 --> 00:04:38.510
officials can't trace anything back
to Goroku's organization.

00:04:38.510 --> 00:04:41.360
Using these methods,

00:04:41.360 --> 00:04:46.430
Goroku has become known as the "Dark Banker".

00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:52.720
He also funnels his dubious earnings
into his own GooSix Co.

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:54.280
And although the money is taxed,

00:04:54.280 --> 00:05:01.020
he can use his laundered earnings
on less shady businesses.

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:05.400
I manage the organization's finances.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:09.650
But after Gido threatened to kill my sister,

00:05:09.650 --> 00:05:12.620
I was forced to send some money his way.

00:05:12.620 --> 00:05:14.000
Wait, what?

00:05:14.770 --> 00:05:16.300
I'm not following.

00:05:16.300 --> 00:05:20.950
Wasn't Gido investigating Goroku undercover?

00:05:20.950 --> 00:05:22.860
I'm sorry, that was a lie.

00:05:22.860 --> 00:05:24.320
A lie?

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:26.620
Gido was a corrupt cop.

00:05:26.620 --> 00:05:31.300
He was selling police intel to Goroku.

00:05:31.300 --> 00:05:34.020
That's why the Inspector was questioning him.

00:05:34.020 --> 00:05:37.250
General Inspector Makita,
also known as the "Grim Reaper".

00:05:37.250 --> 00:05:41.380
Once you've caught his eye,
your career is as good as over.

00:05:41.380 --> 00:05:44.730
He had Gido backed into a corner.

00:05:44.730 --> 00:05:48.960
Did Gido steal the 1 billion yen?

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:52.800
He insisted that wasn't his doing.

00:05:53.940 --> 00:05:57.100
Are you involved in embezzlement as well?

00:06:01.410 --> 00:06:05.290
Yes. And so was my predecessor, Natsumi.

00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:08.260
Say what?

00:06:21.580 --> 00:06:23.400
Give that a look.

00:06:27.300 --> 00:06:31.220
Natsumi worked as Goroku's accountant.

00:06:31.220 --> 00:06:36.380
This was how she embezzled money
for Gido and herself.

00:06:37.720 --> 00:06:40.210
You're lying.

00:06:40.210 --> 00:06:44.580
Three years ago, a syndicate based in Asia

00:06:44.580 --> 00:06:51.320
hired us to transfer a billion yen in cash
to a foreign bank.

00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:55.790
Though it's more common to liquidate cash
by purchasing valuables

00:06:55.790 --> 00:06:59.450
and then sell them at foreign auction houses,

00:06:59.450 --> 00:07:02.160
you're required to pay a high handling fee.

00:07:04.440 --> 00:07:08.740
This is why Goroku was to take the money,

00:07:08.740 --> 00:07:13.450
move it across his bank accounts,
and then transfer it to a foreign bank.

00:07:14.460 --> 00:07:18.340
The organization doesn't deal in cash often.

00:07:18.340 --> 00:07:21.850
Only a few higher-ups
knew of the 1 billion yen.

00:07:21.850 --> 00:07:25.960
Among them, Natsumi was in charge
of monitoring the bills.

00:07:32.830 --> 00:07:37.360
But then someone stole that money.

00:07:37.360 --> 00:07:42.230
The 1 billion yen we were safekeeping...

00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:47.150
has been stolen.

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:50.870
Goroku immediately began searching
for the culprit.

00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:54.760
After all, the money wasn't his.

00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:58.920
He wouldn't want to lose his client's trust.
Or his life.

00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:02.910
That was when Natsumi disappeared.

00:08:02.910 --> 00:08:06.400
Everyone assumed Natsumi ran away
with the money.

00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:12.890
Goroku could only search for her,
while slowly returning his client's money.

00:08:12.890 --> 00:08:17.870
But everything turned on its head
when Natsumi was found dead.

00:08:17.870 --> 00:08:21.860
Someone else had run off
with the 1 billion yen.

00:08:21.860 --> 00:08:24.360
Gido was the first to be suspected.

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:28.900
He was thought to be embezzling money
with Natsumi, after all.

00:08:28.900 --> 00:08:31.790
Did Gido murder her?

00:08:31.790 --> 00:08:37.030
I doubt it. He was desperate to find
the true culprit himself.

00:08:37.030 --> 00:08:38.910
What?

00:08:38.910 --> 00:08:44.580
Eventually, you were incriminated
for murdering your wife.

00:08:44.580 --> 00:08:47.590
Gido said you were being framed,

00:08:47.590 --> 00:08:50.890
but then he himself was killed.

00:08:50.890 --> 00:08:53.720
H-Hold on.

00:08:53.720 --> 00:09:00.020
You turned me into Gido,
despite everything you knew?

00:09:02.580 --> 00:09:05.240
I bet you could have predicted this outcome.

00:09:08.350 --> 00:09:11.430
It was the only way to save you.

00:09:11.430 --> 00:09:13.190
Lies.

00:09:15.570 --> 00:09:19.270
You worked with Gido
to embezzle money from the organization.

00:09:20.680 --> 00:09:26.210
And with Gido gone,
you would be the next suspect.

00:09:26.210 --> 00:09:28.750
So instead, you turned me into Gido.

00:09:32.200 --> 00:09:33.900
That's right.

00:09:35.090 --> 00:09:39.390
I used you to save my own skin.

00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:42.670
You're admitting it?

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:46.870
I changed my face. I lost my family!

00:09:46.870 --> 00:09:48.760
What would you have done
if I was honest from the get-go?

00:09:48.760 --> 00:09:50.590
I wouldn't have rebooted, for one.

00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:54.440
No. You had no other choice at the time.

00:09:54.440 --> 00:09:58.850
Besides, you still have a chance.
Find the real culprit.

00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:01.250
I can't.

00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:06.840
I'll tell Goroku I'm Riku Hayase, not Gido.

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:10.140
He'll kill you.

00:10:10.140 --> 00:10:12.550
I am not Gido.

00:10:12.550 --> 00:10:14.790
This billion-yen fiasco
is none of my business.

00:10:14.790 --> 00:10:19.580
Goroku won't spare anyone
who has intel on the organization.

00:10:19.580 --> 00:10:21.970
I only have 16 hours left to live anyway.

00:10:21.970 --> 00:10:24.380
Then start searching.

00:10:24.380 --> 00:10:27.570
Spend those hours wisely,
because your life depends on it.

00:10:28.170 --> 00:10:32.180
You vowed to see your family again, right?

00:10:35.390 --> 00:10:37.780
Let's work together.

00:10:37.780 --> 00:10:42.290
I promise to protect you.

00:10:44.640 --> 00:10:47.400
You think I can trust you now?

00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:50.850
Please, just leave.

00:10:54.760 --> 00:10:56.620
Leave.

00:11:11.820 --> 00:11:15.060
Hayase's are known for being tenacious.

00:11:16.120 --> 00:11:19.260
That's what your mother told me.

00:11:19.260 --> 00:11:20.460
You can't give up.

00:11:20.460 --> 00:11:24.150
Don't you dare speak about my family.

00:12:18.130 --> 00:12:22.390
[15 hours remaining]

00:12:22.390 --> 00:12:24.170
I only have 15 hours left.

00:12:24.170 --> 00:12:26.730
Damn it, Ichika Kogo tricked me.

00:12:26.730 --> 00:12:30.300
Good morning, Inspector Gido.

00:12:30.300 --> 00:12:33.700
Morning, General Inspector Makita.

00:12:33.700 --> 00:12:36.950
Where'd you get the new scar?

00:12:38.720 --> 00:12:42.750
Fuyuhashi kidnapped me,
and beat me half to death.

00:12:44.280 --> 00:12:48.650
I'm joking. I got drunk and tripped.

00:12:48.650 --> 00:12:51.050
Please, not today, sir.

00:12:51.050 --> 00:12:54.390
I'm still hungover.

00:12:54.390 --> 00:12:56.040
Take care now.

00:13:13.610 --> 00:13:17.630
I have to find a lead,
or else I'll be killed.

00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:20.390
There has to be a hint in Natsumi's case.

00:13:20.390 --> 00:13:25.820
Was Natsumi really involved
in money laundering?

00:13:25.820 --> 00:13:30.910
Not to mention embezzlement...

00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:37.050
Don't get too caught up in the weeds.

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.170
Chief Mikami.

00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.650
The bosses want me to be careful, yeah?

00:13:40.650 --> 00:13:43.730
Take another mental health leave,

00:13:43.730 --> 00:13:47.650
and I'll have to share the blame.

00:13:47.650 --> 00:13:49.360
So how about we hit the town tonight?

00:13:49.360 --> 00:13:53.250
Can't. If I come up dry,
I'll be a dead man tomorrow.

00:13:53.250 --> 00:13:56.540
You're acting like a man obsessed.

00:13:56.540 --> 00:13:59.470
You sure you're all right, Gido?

00:13:59.470 --> 00:14:01.360
- Good morning.
- Morning.

00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:04.850
Sir, we searched for new leads
regarding Natsumi Hayase.

00:14:04.850 --> 00:14:05.690
And?

00:14:05.690 --> 00:14:09.680
Mrs. Natsumi worked as a financial consultant
for several large companies.

00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:13.700
Her clients claim she was a fine worker,

00:14:13.700 --> 00:14:15.870
and she caused no trouble.

00:14:15.870 --> 00:14:18.990
Did she have any ties
to suspicious organizations?

00:14:18.990 --> 00:14:19.960
Pardon?

00:14:19.960 --> 00:14:23.050
Not as far as we're aware, sir.

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:25.110
Right.

00:14:25.110 --> 00:14:28.610
But we did discover Mrs. Natsumi
was involved in an affair.

00:14:30.160 --> 00:14:31.610
You all right?

00:14:31.610 --> 00:14:34.740
Fine.

00:14:34.740 --> 00:14:36.630
Could you elaborate?

00:14:36.630 --> 00:14:40.790
According to one of Mrs. Natsumi's clients,

00:14:40.790 --> 00:14:45.930
she owned two phones,
the second of which was constantly buzzing.

00:14:47.060 --> 00:14:52.190
Another client witnessed her meeting a man
at a hotel as well.

00:14:53.060 --> 00:14:58.030
Her family said she only owned one phone.

00:14:58.030 --> 00:15:00.020
I guess they never knew.

00:15:00.020 --> 00:15:02.100
Do you know who she met with?

00:15:02.100 --> 00:15:06.280
Yes, sir. This is the feed from the hotel.

00:15:09.010 --> 00:15:11.740
Who's this baldie?

00:15:11.740 --> 00:15:16.620
We believe it's this individual here.

00:15:16.620 --> 00:15:19.110
Isamu Kaieda, an attorney.

00:15:19.110 --> 00:15:23.340
He's known for sexually harassing,
and abusing his secretaries.

00:15:23.340 --> 00:15:25.650
His reputation is at a rock bottom.

00:15:25.650 --> 00:15:28.770
However, he has the skills to back his name,

00:15:28.770 --> 00:15:31.710
and has thus received no disciplinary action.

00:15:31.710 --> 00:15:38.040
I'd bet he hooked up
with Mrs. Natsumi as well.

00:15:38.040 --> 00:15:43.840
Then Riku Hayase found out,
and killed his wife in a jealous rage?

00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:46.660
Please don't jump to conclusions.

00:15:46.660 --> 00:15:49.010
Hey now, don't get mad at me.

00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:50.380
Have you managed to reach Kaieda?

00:15:50.380 --> 00:15:53.130
Though we're calling his office,
so far, nothing.

00:15:56.840 --> 00:15:58.280
Figure out where he's hiding.

00:15:58.280 --> 00:15:59.930
I need to see him, today.

00:15:59.930 --> 00:16:01.500
Sir, that's a bit short notice.

00:16:01.500 --> 00:16:04.010
Act fast. I have to see him.

00:16:04.010 --> 00:16:06.230
Where are you going, sir?

00:16:06.230 --> 00:16:08.660
Natsumi Hayase's home.

00:16:08.660 --> 00:16:10.950
Just don't push yourself, you hear?

00:16:10.950 --> 00:16:13.000
He had a nasty scar...

00:16:40.260 --> 00:16:44.080
I'm sorry to make you push yourself, Mom.

00:16:46.580 --> 00:16:52.180
With so many left,
I can guess we're not selling well.

00:16:52.180 --> 00:16:54.000
Wait up, Takumi!

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:55.870
Yeah, don't run!

00:16:55.870 --> 00:16:59.400
Why are you still coming to school?

00:16:59.400 --> 00:17:02.260
Didn't your dad run away?

00:17:02.260 --> 00:17:04.460
You dad abandoned you!
[Son of a murderer]

00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:07.600
Just stop coming to school, stupid.

00:17:08.600 --> 00:17:10.600
Give that back!

00:17:12.680 --> 00:17:14.570
Stop, or I'm telling the teachers.

00:17:14.570 --> 00:17:16.460
- Aw, man.
- Run!

00:17:18.030 --> 00:17:20.490
Ignore them.

00:17:20.490 --> 00:17:23.930
Mizuki, you'll get bullied, too.

00:17:32.730 --> 00:17:34.600
Takumi, right?

00:17:35.580 --> 00:17:37.410
Welcome home.

00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:39.930
You're with the police.

00:17:39.930 --> 00:17:41.480
So you remembered.

00:17:41.480 --> 00:17:44.210
I was on break, but yeah. I'm back.

00:17:49.300 --> 00:17:51.580
Do you tell your teachers about this?

00:17:51.580 --> 00:17:54.390
It's none of your business.

00:17:54.390 --> 00:17:58.050
Does your grandma know?

00:17:58.050 --> 00:18:00.780
Don't you dare tell her.

00:18:00.780 --> 00:18:03.150
She'll worry about it.

00:18:06.570 --> 00:18:08.280
Fine.

00:18:16.580 --> 00:18:18.100
- I'm home.
- Welcome...

00:18:18.100 --> 00:18:20.670
Welcome home, Taku.

00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:23.770
How was school?

00:18:23.770 --> 00:18:24.960
Super fun.

00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:27.540
Good. Now get studying, alright?

00:18:27.540 --> 00:18:30.310
I will. How're you feeling, Grandma?

00:18:30.310 --> 00:18:33.280
Just peachy.

00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:35.700
I'll help after I'm done with homework.

00:18:35.700 --> 00:18:37.440
Thank you, dear.

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:46.840
I'll come back. I promise.

00:18:51.330 --> 00:18:53.530
Welcome.

00:18:55.030 --> 00:18:57.450
Long time no see, ma'am.

00:18:57.450 --> 00:18:59.820
Do you remember me?

00:18:59.820 --> 00:19:02.000
The name's Gido. I'm with the police.

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:05.800
I was put in charge
of Mrs. Natsumi's case again.

00:19:05.800 --> 00:19:08.800
We haven't heard from Riku.

00:19:08.800 --> 00:19:10.740
Please, leave.

00:19:10.740 --> 00:19:13.360
You'll start more rumors in the neighborhood.

00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:15.480
Don't be so cold, ma'am.

00:19:15.480 --> 00:19:19.390
Could I get a cream puff?

00:19:28.630 --> 00:19:30.910
I'll take it as is.

00:19:44.650 --> 00:19:46.700
Yeah, that's a cream puff.

00:19:47.950 --> 00:19:52.360
Since I'm here, could I offer a prayer?

00:20:07.730 --> 00:20:11.050
No need to glare.

00:20:11.050 --> 00:20:16.180
I'm not here to press about Riku Hayase.

00:20:17.430 --> 00:20:22.430
It's entirely possible
there's another perp out there.

00:20:25.660 --> 00:20:30.020
Have you found someone else
who's possibly behind this?

00:20:30.820 --> 00:20:33.310
No, ma'am.

00:20:33.310 --> 00:20:37.840
We must remain level and fair
in our investigating.

00:20:37.840 --> 00:20:45.320
But I can't blame Mr. Riku's own family
for believing he's innocent.

00:20:46.900 --> 00:20:54.680
That's why I've come to ask
about Mrs. Natsumi's disappearance again.

00:20:55.500 --> 00:20:59.110
We asked Mr. Riku about this, of course.

00:20:59.110 --> 00:21:05.230
But was there anything he was unaware of?

00:21:06.900 --> 00:21:11.670
Perhaps something about Mrs. Natsumi's job,

00:21:11.670 --> 00:21:17.560
or maybe... even issues surrounding money?

00:21:22.830 --> 00:21:25.810
This is to prove Mr. Riku's innocence.

00:21:26.920 --> 00:21:29.540
If there's anything you know,
please, tell me.

00:21:34.320 --> 00:21:37.640
Taku, be a dear, and go to your room for me.

00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:51.790
I've never told Riku about this,

00:21:51.790 --> 00:21:58.490
but this store only persisted
because Natsumi lent us her money.

00:22:00.970 --> 00:22:05.310
I would borrow money from Natsumi
to stock our fridges,

00:22:05.310 --> 00:22:11.910
and whenever we found ourselves in the red,
Natsumi would fund our business.

00:22:13.210 --> 00:22:17.320
H-How much did you borrow from her?

00:22:17.320 --> 00:22:21.320
If I include the debts incurred
by the previous owner,

00:22:21.320 --> 00:22:25.840
I would say I borrowed
about 15 million yen in total.

00:22:28.530 --> 00:22:31.630
Why didn't you ever tell Mr. Riku about this?

00:22:31.630 --> 00:22:33.900
Because Natsumi asked me not to.

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:36.130
But still...

00:22:36.130 --> 00:22:41.370
Natsumi said she was at her happiest
watching Riku bake his cakes.

00:22:41.370 --> 00:22:44.390
She didn't want to cause him extra trouble.

00:22:47.900 --> 00:22:51.000
But I had given Natsumi
her fair share of troubles,

00:22:51.000 --> 00:22:55.840
all to protect the livelihood of this store.

00:22:57.400 --> 00:23:02.300
The least I can do now,
is protect the store in her stead.

00:23:06.730 --> 00:23:08.480
What's the matter?

00:23:09.870 --> 00:23:11.820
Nothing.

00:23:12.830 --> 00:23:18.260
I just wonder how Mrs. Natsumi
acquired the money.

00:23:19.060 --> 00:23:21.020
I have no clue myself.

00:23:23.830 --> 00:23:27.580
But Natsumi never complained about it.

00:23:27.580 --> 00:23:33.070
I believe she simply worked hard
for her family's sake.

00:23:36.420 --> 00:23:44.020
Natsumi, did you join Goroku
for the sake of this store?

00:23:46.050 --> 00:23:52.910
[9 hours remaining]

00:24:09.280 --> 00:24:11.600
[Tips for making Cream Puffs]

00:24:22.120 --> 00:24:24.400
- Hello.
- Welcome!

00:24:24.400 --> 00:24:27.030
Could I get eight cream puffs today?

00:24:27.030 --> 00:24:28.760
Of course.

00:24:28.760 --> 00:24:30.100
I'm sorry it's such a large order.

00:24:30.100 --> 00:24:34.290
Oh please, anything for a loyal customer!

00:24:34.900 --> 00:24:35.980
Here you go.

00:24:35.980 --> 00:24:37.110
Thank you.

00:24:37.110 --> 00:24:40.470
Thank you, come again.

00:24:46.740 --> 00:24:51.210
I have no time, but...
Ichika Kogo takes priority.

00:24:59.140 --> 00:25:01.020
Thank you.

00:25:13.420 --> 00:25:15.130
Hello there.

00:25:15.130 --> 00:25:16.030
Hello.

00:25:16.030 --> 00:25:18.890
I've brought some more cream puffs
for you all.

00:25:18.890 --> 00:25:19.810
Really?

00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:22.680
Thank you so much!

00:25:43.740 --> 00:25:46.530
[Ayaka Kogo]

00:26:04.310 --> 00:26:06.410
It's chilly out here. You'll catch a cold.

00:26:06.410 --> 00:26:07.270
[Ayaka Kogo]

00:26:07.270 --> 00:26:09.300
You came again, Ichika?

00:26:09.300 --> 00:26:11.480
You didn't have to, I know you're busy.

00:26:11.480 --> 00:26:15.220
I brought more cream puffs you can't eat.

00:26:15.220 --> 00:26:17.860
Again? Why do you always get those?

00:26:17.860 --> 00:26:21.220
Because the lady there works hard
to make them.

00:26:21.220 --> 00:26:23.280
Let's get some when you're better.

00:26:23.280 --> 00:26:24.630
Sure.

00:26:24.630 --> 00:26:27.510
I'm going to stay out here
a bit longer, okay?

00:26:27.510 --> 00:26:28.700
Okay.

00:26:28.700 --> 00:26:30.480
Then I'll grab you a blanket.

00:26:30.480 --> 00:26:32.030
Thanks.

00:27:02.960 --> 00:27:06.400
Are you alright?

00:27:09.160 --> 00:27:10.880
Can you hear me?

00:27:11.600 --> 00:27:12.350
Excuse me.

00:27:12.350 --> 00:27:13.720
- Yes?
- Excuse me...

00:27:13.720 --> 00:27:14.860
What seems to be the matter?

00:27:14.860 --> 00:27:16.810
- Ayaka?
- This girl collapsed outside.

00:27:16.810 --> 00:27:18.550
- Ayaka!
- Call the doctor.

00:27:18.550 --> 00:27:20.380
It's okay, please bring her over this way.

00:27:20.380 --> 00:27:21.360
Stay with us, Ms. Kogo.

00:27:21.360 --> 00:27:23.780
Her bed is the one in the back.

00:27:23.780 --> 00:27:25.380
Ms. Kogo.

00:27:26.060 --> 00:27:27.310
Ms. Kogo, are you alright?

00:27:27.310 --> 00:27:28.560
Ayaka.

00:27:28.560 --> 00:27:31.060
Ms. Kogo, are you with us?

00:27:31.060 --> 00:27:33.220
Can you hear us?

00:27:33.220 --> 00:27:36.080
I'm listening to her heartbeat.

00:27:36.080 --> 00:27:38.020
- What's her saturation at?
- 90%.

00:27:38.020 --> 00:27:39.330
Bring her an oxygen mask.

00:27:39.330 --> 00:27:40.850
Yes, sir.

00:27:42.950 --> 00:27:48.450
Though she's stabilized,
her saturation's decreased again.

00:27:48.450 --> 00:27:50.620
Will prostacyclin no longer help?

00:27:50.620 --> 00:27:56.020
She's grown immune to it.
It won't be as effective.

00:28:10.110 --> 00:28:12.330
I'll call your sister and doctor right away.

00:28:12.330 --> 00:28:14.050
Don't, I'm fine.

00:28:16.090 --> 00:28:19.020
Are you Gido?

00:28:20.340 --> 00:28:21.810
Yeah.

00:28:23.600 --> 00:28:26.470
You're dating my sister, right?

00:28:29.530 --> 00:28:31.710
I finally got to meet you.

00:28:31.710 --> 00:28:35.830
My sister never wanted to bring you around.

00:28:36.480 --> 00:28:38.710
I see.

00:28:39.980 --> 00:28:43.960
So, what do you like about her?

00:28:43.960 --> 00:28:46.650
What do I... well...

00:28:47.540 --> 00:28:52.000
Her strong will, I suppose.

00:28:53.000 --> 00:28:58.310
She only acts strong.

00:28:58.310 --> 00:29:01.050
Be there for her when she needs it, okay?

00:29:09.720 --> 00:29:12.010
Ayaka.

00:29:12.010 --> 00:29:13.760
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

00:29:17.860 --> 00:29:22.450
You almost gave me a heart attack.

00:29:22.450 --> 00:29:23.770
Yes?

00:29:23.770 --> 00:29:25.300
She's conscious.

00:29:25.300 --> 00:29:27.390
I'll call the doctor right away.

00:29:27.390 --> 00:29:29.020
Thank you.

00:29:29.800 --> 00:29:32.160
They say no more going outside for you.

00:29:32.160 --> 00:29:36.050
And especially not alone.

00:29:36.050 --> 00:29:41.450
Too bad. Time to install another dating app.

00:29:44.670 --> 00:29:48.690
Gido seems like a nice guy.

00:29:48.690 --> 00:29:51.350
He saved my life, too.

00:29:57.610 --> 00:29:59.570
You tailed me.

00:30:01.270 --> 00:30:03.040
So, your sister...

00:30:07.580 --> 00:30:11.410
The least you could do
is tell me a bit about yourself.

00:30:15.250 --> 00:30:19.460
She has pulmonary arterial hypertension.

00:30:19.460 --> 00:30:23.640
One of the arteries connecting her heart
to her lungs is thinner,

00:30:23.640 --> 00:30:27.500
which cause symptoms similar
to heart failures.

00:30:28.700 --> 00:30:30.580
Has she been hospitalized her whole life?

00:30:33.230 --> 00:30:37.800
The only cure is to replace her lungs.

00:30:38.900 --> 00:30:42.380
She's on the donor waitlist right now.

00:30:43.950 --> 00:30:49.760
The operation would take place in the US,
and I need money to get her there.

00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:54.730
Is that why you've been embezzling funds
from Goroku's organization?

00:30:57.950 --> 00:31:02.260
Your sister wouldn't appreciate being saved
with tainted money.

00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:04.790
Don't bother trying to convince me otherwise.

00:31:04.790 --> 00:31:07.990
I would do anything to save my sister.

00:31:13.730 --> 00:31:20.480
If Gido is found guilty of theft,
my embezzling will be discovered as well.

00:31:20.480 --> 00:31:22.940
But I can't afford to die now.

00:31:26.330 --> 00:31:28.590
Let's join forces again.

00:31:29.450 --> 00:31:33.240
You'll get more intel on the culprit
with my help.

00:31:43.140 --> 00:31:46.380
[Adachi: We've tracked down Kaieda.]

00:31:46.380 --> 00:31:48.740
You suspect Kaieda?

00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:54.380
I'm not working with you.

00:31:54.380 --> 00:31:56.410
You're not trustworthy.

00:31:57.730 --> 00:32:00.670
My advice? Don't give them this.

00:32:01.640 --> 00:32:06.480
[Tips for making Cream Puffs]
You'll get your family involved.

00:32:07.590 --> 00:32:09.070
Don't take stuff from me.

00:32:09.070 --> 00:32:12.260
Then don't tail me.

00:32:21.630 --> 00:32:24.220
Kaieda uses his vast wealth

00:32:24.220 --> 00:32:27.160
to frequent clubs every night.

00:32:27.940 --> 00:32:30.260
According to one hostess he visits,

00:32:30.260 --> 00:32:35.760
Kaieda's been lending his name
to a "Clearance Law Office".

00:32:35.760 --> 00:32:41.070
[4 hours 45 minutes remaining]

00:32:45.160 --> 00:32:48.790
Find us the real culprit, money and all.

00:32:48.790 --> 00:32:51.010
You have until midnight.

00:32:52.970 --> 00:32:55.080
Good evening, Inspector Gido.

00:32:55.970 --> 00:32:56.970
Why're you here?

00:32:56.970 --> 00:32:59.740
I was waiting here in hopes you'd arrive.

00:32:59.740 --> 00:33:03.220
Kaieda went into the building 30 minutes ago.

00:33:04.610 --> 00:33:05.930
Where's Teramoto?

00:33:05.930 --> 00:33:07.680
He clocked out on time.

00:33:07.680 --> 00:33:08.820
And you won't?

00:33:08.820 --> 00:33:10.890
Certainly not.

00:33:10.890 --> 00:33:15.210
Frankly speaking, I thought investigations
meant nothing to you, sir.

00:33:15.210 --> 00:33:16.930
I'm happy to see I was proven wrong.

00:33:16.930 --> 00:33:19.160
Tailing me won't get you far.

00:33:19.160 --> 00:33:20.660
You could even die.

00:33:20.660 --> 00:33:25.040
Risks are necessary to find out the truth.

00:33:25.040 --> 00:33:28.420
I'm doing this so justice prevails, sir.

00:33:28.420 --> 00:33:29.810
Adachi.

00:33:29.810 --> 00:33:31.070
Yes, sir?

00:33:31.070 --> 00:33:33.420
You're an upstanding officer.

00:33:34.040 --> 00:33:35.670
Thank you, sir.

00:33:41.130 --> 00:33:41.870
Ready?

00:33:41.870 --> 00:33:43.270
Yes, sir.

00:33:48.550 --> 00:33:50.700
Police.

00:33:51.300 --> 00:33:53.850
Where's Mr. Kaieda?

00:34:00.050 --> 00:34:04.430
If I recall, this woman is... "Machi".

00:34:04.430 --> 00:34:06.770
An old friend of Fuyuhashi,

00:34:06.770 --> 00:34:11.210
who wrangles up the young folk
working under him.

00:34:11.210 --> 00:34:13.990
Machi knows of "Gido".

00:34:16.150 --> 00:34:17.790
Gido, Tokyo Metropolitan Police.

00:34:17.790 --> 00:34:20.130
Adachi. Mr. Kaieda is here, is he not?

00:34:20.130 --> 00:34:22.500
I reckon he's in that room.

00:34:22.500 --> 00:34:23.620
Why have you come?

00:34:23.620 --> 00:34:25.250
We've got business with him.

00:34:25.250 --> 00:34:28.020
Mr. Kaieda is not - hey!

00:34:30.380 --> 00:34:32.960
Machi.

00:34:33.670 --> 00:34:38.800
Didn't I say no visitors?

00:34:38.800 --> 00:34:40.470
Sorry, sir. The police here insisted.

00:34:40.470 --> 00:34:43.280
You must be Mr. Kaieda.

00:34:43.280 --> 00:34:44.710
Tokyo Metropolitan Police, Gido.

00:34:44.710 --> 00:34:45.850
Likewise, Adachi.

00:34:45.850 --> 00:34:48.440
What brings you here at this hour?

00:34:48.440 --> 00:34:52.130
There's no law
against having fun after hours.

00:34:52.130 --> 00:34:55.130
We have questions about Natsumi Hayase.

00:34:55.130 --> 00:34:59.010
Sir, you were rather close with her, no?

00:35:00.290 --> 00:35:04.360
Beats me. I've been forgetful nowadays.

00:35:04.360 --> 00:35:07.200
We know you two met at a hotel, sir.

00:35:07.200 --> 00:35:09.820
Did we, now?

00:35:10.920 --> 00:35:13.100
Ah, apologies.

00:35:13.100 --> 00:35:17.580
Miss, could you step out?
I'll make myself presentable.

00:35:24.790 --> 00:35:28.440
What are you playing at, Gido?

00:35:35.520 --> 00:35:40.260
You're trampling onto Goroku's turf.

00:35:40.260 --> 00:35:45.230
Ain't it your job to keep the officers
off our trail?

00:35:45.230 --> 00:35:46.520
Goroku won't be happy.

00:35:46.520 --> 00:35:48.470
Not like I've got long to live.

00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:51.590
I see. So you're rebelling.

00:35:51.590 --> 00:35:56.020
Natsumi Hayase's death and the missing cash
are connected.

00:35:56.630 --> 00:36:02.730
Tell me what you know
of her disappearance three years ago.

00:36:02.730 --> 00:36:05.210
I don't know a thing.

00:36:17.280 --> 00:36:20.180
A dead man is a desperate man, Kaieda.

00:36:20.180 --> 00:36:23.730
A-Alright, I'll talk, I'll talk!

00:36:27.210 --> 00:36:29.110
Why did you go to see Natsumi?

00:36:29.110 --> 00:36:32.480
I was having her embezzle money for me
from the organization.

00:36:32.480 --> 00:36:35.830
I blackmailed her.
Said I'd tell her family everything.

00:36:38.050 --> 00:36:39.380
Scumbag.

00:36:39.380 --> 00:36:41.250
Like you're so innocent.

00:36:41.250 --> 00:36:45.740
You blackmailed her for the very same reason.

00:36:53.660 --> 00:36:55.240
You stole the billion yen.

00:36:55.240 --> 00:36:56.960
No, that, I didn't do.

00:36:56.960 --> 00:36:59.130
You murdered Natsumi!

00:36:59.130 --> 00:37:03.230
Course not. I owed her my life.

00:37:03.230 --> 00:37:08.080
Why would I kill the woman
who was getting me money?

00:37:09.860 --> 00:37:13.580
You're going to tell Goroku
everything you did to Natsumi.

00:37:13.580 --> 00:37:16.170
Calm down for a second.

00:37:16.170 --> 00:37:20.640
If anything, Ichika's the suspicious one.

00:37:23.110 --> 00:37:24.340
Why's that?

00:37:24.340 --> 00:37:26.920
Use your brain, Gido.

00:37:26.920 --> 00:37:31.340
She replaced Natsumi,
and now handles the organization's money.

00:37:31.340 --> 00:37:34.180
She's the one really benefitting
from Natsumi's death.

00:37:35.660 --> 00:37:38.650
Are you saying Ichika murdered Natsumi,
and made off with the billion yen?

00:37:38.650 --> 00:37:40.280
That's right.

00:37:41.920 --> 00:37:43.020
Where's your proof?

00:37:43.020 --> 00:37:46.310
I don't got any.
Press her, and you'll get answers.

00:37:46.310 --> 00:37:49.440
But Goroku won't let that slide.

00:37:49.440 --> 00:37:53.050
Ichika's hard to replace, after all.

00:37:54.960 --> 00:37:59.310
If you choose to press Ichika instead,

00:37:59.310 --> 00:38:03.590
I'll give you my support at tonight's dinner.

00:38:03.590 --> 00:38:07.360
That'll convince Goroku to take action.

00:38:07.360 --> 00:38:12.680
Us embezzlers should work together, eh?

00:38:15.220 --> 00:38:22.050
Gido, the only way you're saving your skin,
is by sacrificing Ichika.

00:38:37.310 --> 00:38:38.540
Hello?

00:38:38.540 --> 00:38:41.590
Feeling better?

00:38:41.590 --> 00:38:43.470
Fuyuhashi.

00:38:43.470 --> 00:38:47.370
I'm sending you an address.
Come quick, you've got work to do.

00:38:47.370 --> 00:38:49.810
You know I've got no time for jobs now.

00:38:49.810 --> 00:38:52.680
Your circumstances don't matter.

00:38:52.680 --> 00:38:55.300
The organization's orders are absolute.

00:38:59.380 --> 00:39:01.600
Fuyuhashi speaks for Goroku.

00:39:01.600 --> 00:39:03.820
You'd better hurry on now.

00:39:05.810 --> 00:39:11.690
I'll see you later, Gido.
Let's expose Ichika together, eh?

00:39:20.130 --> 00:39:22.140
Sir?

00:39:22.140 --> 00:39:24.680
We're ending things here for the night.

00:39:25.680 --> 00:39:30.330
[4 hours 28 minutes remaining]

00:39:30.330 --> 00:39:31.750
[GooSix Co.]

00:39:31.750 --> 00:39:34.570
Looks good. Let's call it for the tonight.

00:39:34.570 --> 00:39:35.810
Phew...

00:39:35.810 --> 00:39:37.850
Great work, everybody.

00:39:37.850 --> 00:39:41.520
Here, get yourselves a nice dinner.
You all deserve it.

00:39:41.520 --> 00:39:43.900
- Here.
- Thank you, sir.

00:39:43.900 --> 00:39:47.590
Mr. Goroku's covering dinner for us tonight!

00:39:47.590 --> 00:39:48.730
Thank you, sir.

00:39:48.730 --> 00:39:51.370
Don't feel obligated to go though.
If you've got plans, prioritize them.

00:39:51.370 --> 00:39:52.370
Have a good night.

00:39:52.370 --> 00:39:54.500
- You too, sir.
- Thank you.

00:40:00.530 --> 00:40:02.290
What did you need?

00:40:02.290 --> 00:40:04.940
I wanted to talk about Gido.

00:40:04.940 --> 00:40:09.800
You gave him a midnight deadline
with his life on the line.

00:40:09.800 --> 00:40:12.240
No need to talk about that here.

00:40:12.240 --> 00:40:14.870
He's not finding the culprit
in less than four hours, sir.

00:40:14.870 --> 00:40:19.740
Then I never needed him in the first place.

00:40:19.740 --> 00:40:22.010
But sir...

00:40:23.680 --> 00:40:26.910
What brings you here tonight, Mr. Kaieda?

00:40:26.910 --> 00:40:30.020
You've driven Gido up a wall, Mr. Goroku.

00:40:30.020 --> 00:40:34.390
He even came barging into my firm.

00:40:34.390 --> 00:40:37.080
Surely he's gone too far.

00:40:37.080 --> 00:40:43.290
I understand police intel is valuable,
but it may give us issues in the future.

00:40:43.290 --> 00:40:46.340
That is my warning to you
as your legal consultant.

00:40:46.340 --> 00:40:48.200
- Thank you, Mr. Kaieda.
- Of course.

00:40:48.200 --> 00:40:51.150
I will see you both at dinner tonight.

00:40:55.620 --> 00:40:57.590
- Take care, sir.
- Will do.

00:41:02.690 --> 00:41:08.690
If Gido's caught,
things will get dicey for you, Ichika.

00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:19.040
I know you've both taken money
from the organization.

00:41:26.210 --> 00:41:30.590
You're currently Gido's prime suspect.

00:41:30.590 --> 00:41:35.130
He'll press you at dinner tonight.

00:41:35.130 --> 00:41:39.200
But if I take your side,
you'll get off scot-free.

00:41:40.650 --> 00:41:42.950
Why not jump ship to me?

00:41:46.470 --> 00:41:50.800
Gido stole the billion yen,
and murdered Natsumi.

00:41:51.530 --> 00:41:54.790
Make the accusation,
and I'll back your claim.

00:42:03.020 --> 00:42:08.850
[3 hours 10 minutes remaining]

00:42:15.160 --> 00:42:18.950
Shut up already.

00:42:25.300 --> 00:42:27.510
Evening.

00:42:29.090 --> 00:42:30.940
Thanks again.

00:43:15.620 --> 00:43:20.790
That just now
was one of Goroku's "part-timers".

00:43:22.590 --> 00:43:28.540
Some folks try to use their accounts
to make the organization's money their own.

00:43:28.540 --> 00:43:31.120
That's what happens
to the ones who get caught.

00:43:34.150 --> 00:43:37.160
Once their families file
a missing persons report,

00:43:37.160 --> 00:43:42.970
Gido would inform the organization
of their search.

00:43:48.970 --> 00:43:51.390
It's almost midnight.

00:43:53.500 --> 00:43:56.440
I'll tell you how to save your skin.

00:43:58.220 --> 00:44:00.590
Blame everything on me.

00:44:01.710 --> 00:44:02.930
What?

00:44:02.930 --> 00:44:06.040
Tell them I tricked Natsumi,
stole the money,

00:44:06.040 --> 00:44:10.010
and then murdered her to take her place.

00:44:10.010 --> 00:44:12.400
But if I do that...

00:44:12.400 --> 00:44:16.980
Don't worry,
I'll find a way out of the situation.

00:44:16.980 --> 00:44:20.460
So don't you dare run away on me.

00:44:32.660 --> 00:44:34.680
Fine, I'll work with you.

00:44:34.680 --> 00:44:36.760
I knew you were a smart cookie, Ichika.

00:44:36.760 --> 00:44:40.090
Say, let's strategize in private before dinner.

00:44:40.090 --> 00:44:41.980
I'll show you something good.

00:44:44.350 --> 00:44:49.950
These are records proving Gido used Natsumi
to embezzle money three years ago.

00:44:49.950 --> 00:44:51.050
[Deposit Receipts]

00:44:51.050 --> 00:44:56.570
Show this to Goroku, and it's over for Gido.

00:44:56.570 --> 00:44:58.960
And why do you have these records?

00:44:58.960 --> 00:45:02.430
I took them for myself
when Natsumi disappeared.

00:45:04.970 --> 00:45:12.070
Replace my name in the blue with Gido's,
and you're set to go.

00:45:12.070 --> 00:45:17.710
Bring this to Goroku's attention,
and you'll surely earn his trust.

00:45:18.860 --> 00:45:20.540
I'll put it to good use.

00:45:20.540 --> 00:45:24.690
Excellent. That seals our partnership - ouch.

00:45:25.990 --> 00:45:29.520
Here, let me open a nice wine for us.

00:45:34.730 --> 00:45:37.490
I'll tell you how to save your skin.

00:45:37.490 --> 00:45:39.530
Blame everything on me.

00:45:39.530 --> 00:45:42.400
Tell them I tricked Natsumi,
stole the money,

00:45:42.400 --> 00:45:45.590
and then murdered her to take her place.

00:45:45.590 --> 00:45:48.360
Ichika's proposition was a lie.

00:45:48.360 --> 00:45:50.700
She's trying to set me up.

00:45:50.700 --> 00:45:54.700
I have to run.
That's the only way I'm surviving.

00:45:55.590 --> 00:45:57.650
But before I disappear...

00:46:11.060 --> 00:46:13.130
- Give that a taste.
- Okay.

00:46:14.650 --> 00:46:17.600
- Doesn't that taste like your father's?
- Yeah.

00:46:17.600 --> 00:46:19.770
Let's give it another go.

00:46:19.770 --> 00:46:22.030
Here, pour in the milk.

00:46:32.790 --> 00:46:34.900
What brings you here at this hour?

00:46:34.900 --> 00:46:37.810
Did you change your custard recipe?

00:46:37.810 --> 00:46:39.480
Pardon?

00:46:39.480 --> 00:46:44.420
Well... Baking's actually a hobby of mine.

00:46:45.040 --> 00:46:48.660
Do you include a vanilla bean
when you boil the milk?

00:46:48.660 --> 00:46:52.940
Yes, I was told it helps with the scent.

00:46:52.940 --> 00:46:56.540
Have you changed the amount of eggs
you add to the choux batter?

00:46:56.540 --> 00:47:03.290
Yes. On dry days,
I was told to add more eggs.

00:47:03.290 --> 00:47:05.030
Told, by who?

00:47:05.030 --> 00:47:08.380
A regular of ours.

00:47:08.380 --> 00:47:09.740
A regular?

00:47:09.740 --> 00:47:12.980
Yes, she's quite the dessert expert.

00:47:12.980 --> 00:47:16.840
She even stopped by a second time today
to give us advice.

00:47:16.840 --> 00:47:19.420
She helped us recreate Dad's flavor.

00:47:19.420 --> 00:47:21.450
Yes, exactly.

00:47:21.450 --> 00:47:25.770
We couldn't believe our cream puffs
now taste just like my son's.

00:47:25.770 --> 00:47:29.110
Who gave you the advice?

00:47:29.110 --> 00:47:32.570
A lovely woman named Ichika Kogo.

00:47:33.270 --> 00:47:36.020
My advice? Don't give them this.

00:47:45.750 --> 00:47:47.220
Here.

00:47:51.020 --> 00:47:53.970
Try it. It tastes just like my Dad's custard.

00:48:03.410 --> 00:48:05.230
How is it?

00:48:08.530 --> 00:48:10.680
It tastes...

00:48:11.860 --> 00:48:14.590
like kindness.

00:48:14.590 --> 00:48:16.190
Right?

00:48:16.190 --> 00:48:21.370
Such a kindhearted man cannot be a murderer.

00:48:22.910 --> 00:48:27.480
My dad didn't kill my mom.

00:48:27.480 --> 00:48:29.190
I know he didn't.

00:49:05.740 --> 00:49:08.230
Could I get your gun?

00:49:18.390 --> 00:49:20.960
It's time for dinner.

00:49:20.960 --> 00:49:23.320
I know.

00:49:23.320 --> 00:49:25.700
I was on my way.

00:49:56.520 --> 00:49:58.040
Evening.

00:49:58.040 --> 00:49:59.960
Good evening, sir.

00:50:16.050 --> 00:50:21.040
Two nights in a row of your cooking?
What an honor.

00:50:21.040 --> 00:50:22.550
I must agree.

00:50:22.550 --> 00:50:24.650
I've got another luxury ingredient tonight.

00:50:28.660 --> 00:50:32.400
Gido, you liked lobster, no?

00:50:47.100 --> 00:50:49.930
Ichika, do you have any further updates?

00:50:49.930 --> 00:50:55.440
I have not found any accounts nor safes
made under Natsumi's name.

00:50:55.440 --> 00:51:00.710
Furthermore, I have no record
stating the money went to Natsumi either.

00:51:00.710 --> 00:51:05.950
Then someone else must have stolen the money,

00:51:05.950 --> 00:51:09.180
and silenced Natsumi instead.

00:51:09.180 --> 00:51:14.270
Guess we can be certain it's Gido.

00:51:14.270 --> 00:51:19.210
Disappearing for half a year
doesn't help your case either.

00:51:20.160 --> 00:51:25.070
How about it, Gido?
Can you prove your innocence?

00:51:28.570 --> 00:51:33.300
Here, one last delicious meal for the road.

00:51:42.280 --> 00:51:44.380
Half a year ago...

00:51:45.510 --> 00:51:50.830
I made myself scarce,
because I thought I was a dead man.

00:51:54.560 --> 00:51:57.120
And yet, I crawled back here.

00:51:57.740 --> 00:52:00.210
Know why?

00:52:05.240 --> 00:52:09.890
It's to expose the true culprit.

00:52:24.850 --> 00:52:27.060
You're the one behind it all, aren't you?

00:52:31.710 --> 00:52:33.800
Mr. Kaieda.

00:52:37.020 --> 00:52:40.670
That's your last resort? Pathetic.

00:52:40.670 --> 00:52:44.930
You blackmailed Natsumi
to help embezzle the organization's money.

00:52:44.930 --> 00:52:48.270
I was having her embezzle money for me
from the organization.

00:52:48.270 --> 00:52:51.660
I blackmailed her.
Said I'd tell her family everything.

00:52:53.420 --> 00:52:57.100
You threatened me to say that at gunpoint.

00:52:57.100 --> 00:52:59.300
This recording proves nothing.

00:52:59.300 --> 00:53:04.080
If anything, you're the one
who had Natsumi embezzling money.

00:53:04.080 --> 00:53:06.300
We all know the rumors.

00:53:06.300 --> 00:53:11.380
Don't you have any record of that, Ichika?

00:53:12.160 --> 00:53:18.030
After re-evaluating some numbers,
I did come across an anomaly.

00:53:18.780 --> 00:53:24.470
Three years ago, Natsumi embezzled money
from the organization.

00:53:24.470 --> 00:53:27.090
We lost a grand total of 68 million yen.

00:53:27.770 --> 00:53:31.230
It says here the money went to you,
Mr. Kaieda.

00:53:32.650 --> 00:53:34.370
What?

00:53:34.370 --> 00:53:38.020
These are some records Natsumi left behind.

00:53:40.980 --> 00:53:45.840
Lies! This was proof of Gido's embezzling.

00:53:45.840 --> 00:53:47.440
You swapped our names.

00:53:47.440 --> 00:53:51.460
Mr. Kaieda, please.
Enjoy this delicious meal.

00:53:55.590 --> 00:53:58.530
Sir, I'm sorry. I only took a couple million.

00:53:58.530 --> 00:54:00.640
But I know nothing of the missing billion.

00:54:00.640 --> 00:54:03.400
I didn't kill Natsumi either!

00:54:10.060 --> 00:54:14.150
Your suspicions aren't cleared yet, Gido.

00:54:14.150 --> 00:54:17.400
Especially since the missing cash
still remains at large.

00:54:17.950 --> 00:54:20.920
But I admit,
you brought us a lead today.

00:54:20.920 --> 00:54:23.880
I shall give you passing marks for the night.

00:54:27.060 --> 00:54:29.720
Eat up while it's hot.

00:54:29.720 --> 00:54:32.090
- Thank you, sir.
- Much appreciated.

00:54:47.280 --> 00:54:51.980
What was your plan if I had blamed you?

00:54:52.700 --> 00:54:56.510
I would've tried to pin the blame on Kaieda.

00:54:56.510 --> 00:54:58.540
What a reckless move.

00:54:58.540 --> 00:55:00.340
I know.

00:55:00.340 --> 00:55:05.250
That data wouldn't have been convincing enough.

00:55:06.060 --> 00:55:11.160
But your recording dealt the finishing blow.

00:55:11.160 --> 00:55:12.860
Thank you.

00:55:21.090 --> 00:55:23.040
I knew.

00:55:25.080 --> 00:55:30.300
I knew rebooting would put you in danger.

00:55:33.060 --> 00:55:41.040
But I vowed to protect you
for getting involved.

00:55:44.220 --> 00:55:45.840
So...

00:55:49.480 --> 00:55:54.210
I want us to join forces again.

00:55:56.160 --> 00:56:00.590
Were you lying about being Gido's lover?

00:56:01.240 --> 00:56:02.980
Yes.

00:56:04.130 --> 00:56:09.260
It was a front
to keep our embezzling a secret.

00:56:10.520 --> 00:56:15.050
Otherwise our frequent meet-ups
would make Goroku suspicious.

00:56:31.020 --> 00:56:35.480
These are the revised cream puffs.
They followed your advice.

00:56:52.140 --> 00:56:53.990
Bon appétit.

00:56:55.330 --> 00:56:57.310
Thanks.

00:57:14.820 --> 00:57:17.470
I've decided to trust you, Ichika.

00:57:20.310 --> 00:57:25.660
Let's both survive for our family's sake.

00:58:56.730 --> 00:58:57.800
I don't care about that woman.

00:58:57.800 --> 00:58:59.180
Weren't you going to believe me?

00:58:59.180 --> 00:59:00.270
You're hiding something.

00:59:00.270 --> 00:59:02.340
Show me the proof.

00:59:02.340 --> 00:59:04.240
Let's end this.

00:59:04.240 --> 00:59:06.760
We must survive, for our family's sake.